author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: Gunfire erupts after Migos beat up Sean Kingston at Nevada event - NY Daily News
text:
Migos apparently aren’t looking to make any new amigos.
The rowdy Georgia rap trio allegedly got into a brawl with Jamaican R&B singer Sean Kingston while attending an event at the Sands Expo and Convention Center in Las Vegas on Tuesday afternoon, according to TMZ . The fight broke up after somebody in Kingston’s camp pulled out a gun and fired a single shot, not hitting anyone.
The “Look at My Dab” group supposedly wrestled Kingston to the ground and began stomping his head around 4 p.m., police sources told the gossip site. The fight had apparently erupted after an argument about fellow hip-hop artist Soulja Boy turned heated.
A Las Vegas Police Department spokesman told the Daily News that the alleged shooter and one other person were taken into custody after the fisticuff. Their charges weren’t immediately available.
